import { Component, EventEmitter, Input, Output } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'planet-list',
  templateUrl: 'planet-list.component.html',
  styleUrls: [ 'planet-list.component.css' ]
})
export class PlanetListComponent {
  @Input() public planets$: any;
  @Input() public isCollapsed: boolean;
  @Output() public toggledChange: EventEmitter<number> = new EventEmitter<number>();

  public loaded$ = true;

  public columns = [
    { prop: 'id' },
    { prop: 'name' },
    { prop: 'diameter' }
  ];

}

<div>
    <ngx-datatable #planetList class="bootstrap"
                [rows]="planets$ | async"
                [sorts]="[{prop: 'id', dir: 'asc'}]"
                [columnMode]="'force'"
                [headerHeight]="40"
                [summaryPosition]="'bottom'"
                [footerHeight]="40"
                [limit]="15"
                [rowHeight]="'auto'">

        <ngx-datatable-column name="Name of the planet / Species present there" prop="name">
            <ng-template let-value="value" let-row="row" ngx-datatable-cell-template>
                <b>{{value}}</b> <br>
                <u>Species</u>:
                <span *ngFor="let species of row.species">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary species-button" (click)="toggledChange.emit(species.id-1)"
                   [attr.aria-expanded]="!isCollapsed" aria-controls="collapseSide">{{species.name}}</button>
                </span>
            </ng-template>
        </ngx-datatable-column>
        <ngx-datatable-column name="Diameter (km)" prop="diameter">
            <ng-template let-value="value" ngx-datatable-cell-template>
                {{value}}
            </ng-template>
        </ngx-datatable-column>

    </ngx-datatable>
</div>
